file: easycron-v1/README

easycron
========

This is a utility for modifying a user's crontab

Easycron's  main  usage  is  to  add processes to the user's crontab without having to know the format that crontab accepts. For example, easycron 30min './example.sh' adds the ./example.sh process to the crontab to run every 30 min.

to install, run: sudo ./install.sh

